gland, but fell out of favour in the 16th century until it was revived in the 20th century. Little Hugh of Lincoln was a child supposed in the Middle Ages to have been murdered by Jews in about  1255 , a legend responsible for several outbursts of anti-Semitism at various times. The story is referred to by  Chaucer  in The Prioress's Tale. He is not to be confused with  St Hugh of Lincoln  (  1140–1200 ), bishop of Lincoln (  1186–1200 ), who was noted for his charity and good works, his piety, and his defence of the Church against the State. Since the later Middle Ages <i>Hugh</i> has also been used as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Aodh ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Hugh Finderne was born before 1350, his father, John I Findern, was 11346 and his mother, Catherine Findern, was 14. He had at least 3 sons and 1 daughter with Aline Willington Heiress. He died after 1395, and was buried in All Saints' Church, Findern, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Bef 1350–Aft 1395":"enne 1350–pärast 1395","1350–1395":"1350–1395","1353–1394":"1353–1394","1365–1413":"1365–1413","1390–1444":"1390–1444","1395–1445":"1395–1445","–1306":"–1306","1338–1360":"1338–1360","1335–Female":"1335–Surnud","1395":"1395","1394":"1394","1350":"1350","1360":"1360","1390":"1390","1338":"1338","Bef 1350":"enne 1350","1413":"1413","1335":"1335","1445":"1445","1444":"1444","1365":"1365","1353":"1353","Aft 1394":"pärast 1394","Aft 1395":"pärast 1395","1306":"1306","All Saints' Church, Findern, South Derbyshire district, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom":"All Saints' Church, Findern, Derbyshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Findern, Derbyshire, England":"Findern, Derbyshire, England","Findern Manor, Findern, South Derbyshire district, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom":"Findern, Derbyshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Finderne, Derbyshire, England":"Derbyshire, England"},"fi":{"Bef 1350–Aft 1395":"ennen vuotta 1350–1395 jälkeen","1350–1395":"1350–1395","1353–1394":"1353–13